''''Clivia'''' is a German [[apple]] [[cultivar]]. It was created at the Institut für Acker- und Pflanzenbau of [[Müncheberg]],<ref name=heinz/> in [[Märkisch-Oderland]] in eastern Germany, which at that time was in the [[German Democratic Republic]]. It is a [[Hybrid (biology)|hybrid]] of '[[Geheimrat Dr. Oldenburg]]' and '[[Cox's Orange Pippin]]'. It was reported as a new variety in 1964<ref name=cnr/> and 1965;<ref name=neues/> it was parent of a new cultivar, '[[Pinova]]', in 1965.<ref name=obst/>

==Hybrids==
Cultivars that descend from 'Clivia' include: [[Pilot (apple)|'Pilot']] ('Clivia' &times; [[Undine (apple)|'Undine']]); 'Pinova' ('Clivia' &times; '[[Golden Delicious]]'); '[[Rubinstep]]' ('Clivia' &times; [[Rubin (apple)|'Rubin']]);<ref name=mol/>{{Rp|539}} and '[[Reanda]]'.<ref name=mol/>{{Rp|538}}

